y%20a%200.9-point%20margin%20(49.7%25%20to%2048.8%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20weren't%20blowouts%2C%20but%20even%20a%20small%20shift%20was%20enough%20to%20hand%20Trump%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20Harris%20didn't%20win%20any%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-are-2024-presidential-election-swing-states-trump-harris-polls-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emajor%20swing%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year%2C%20which%20made%20it%20mathematically%20impossible%20for%20her%20to%20get%20to%20270%20electoral%20votes%20after%20the%20blue%20wall%20fell%20and%20GOP-leaning%20states%20stayed%20true%20to%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225265%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Donald%20Trump%20in%20Michigan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6730f26888cea3ba1c1f8da7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223510%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20was%20a%20frequent%20visitor%20to%20Michigan%20during%20the%202024%20campaign.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FAlex%20Brandon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4a27156-65ec-4186-a28c-35d049e48d6a%5C%22%3EHarris'%20suburban%20performance%20wasn't%20strong%20enough%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDemocrats%20went%20into%20the%20election%20hoping%20to%20make%20historic%20gains%20with%20suburban%20voters.%20The%20party%20believed%20those%20voters%20would%20continue%20to%20reject%20Trump's%20political%20brand%20as%20they%20did%20in%202018%2C%202020%2C%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20unlike%202020%2C%20when%20Biden%20won%20the%20suburbs%20by%20two%20points%20(50%25%20to%2048%25)%20nationally%2C%20Trump%20this%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2Finteractive%2F2024%2Fpolitics%2F2020-2016-exit-polls-2024-dg%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewon%20suburban%20voters%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20four%20points%20(51%25%20to%2047%25)%2C%20according%20to%20exit%20polling%20conducted%20by%20Edison%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20blue%20wall%2C%20Harris%20performed%20well%20in%20many%20key%20counties%2C%20including%20Oakland%20County%2C%20just%20outside%20Detroit%3B%20Montgomery%20County%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20an%20affluent%20county%20adjacent%20to%20Philadelphia%3B%20and%20Dane%20County%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20Wisconsin%20capital%20of%20Madison%20and%20its%20surrounding%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20wasn't%20enough%20to%20offset%20Trump's%20rural%20and%20exurban%20strength%2C%20as%20well%20as%20his%20better-than-expected%20retention%20of%20support%20in%20critical%20areas%20like%20Waukesha%20County%2C%20Wisconsin%2C%20a%20suburban%20jurisdiction%20close%20to%20Milwaukee%2C%20and%20Bucks%20County%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20a%20crucial%20swing%20county%20near%20Philadelphia.%20Harris%20also%20had%20to%20overcome%20Trump's%20increased%20vote%20share%20with%20minority%20voters%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fyoung-black-latino-men-trump-economy-jobs-9184ca85b1651f06fd555ab2df7982b5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enotably%20among%20Black%20men%20and%20Latinos%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20cut%20into%20her%20margins%20in%20many%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Harris%20won%20Oakland%20County%20by%2010%20points.%20But%20Biden%20won%20it%20by%2014%20points%20in%202020.%20In%20a%20populous%20county%20filled%20with%20the%20sort%20of%20college-educated%20independents%20and%20disaffected%20Republicans%20that%20the%20Harris%20campaign%20was%20targeting%2C%20the%20vice%20president's%20margins%20had%20to%20be%20higher%20to%20counter%20Trump's%20gains%20in%20places%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F11%2F03%2Fus%2Fsaginaw-michigan-election.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESaginaw%20County%2C%20Michigan%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20politically%20competitive%20jurisdiction%20that%20he%20won%20this%20year%20after%20losing%20it%20to%20Biden%20four%20years%