%3EToothacre%20said%20it's%20good%20to%20have%20a%20pad%20of%20paper%20and%20a%20pen%20with%20you%20to%20take%20notes%20or%20work%20things%20out%20during%20the%20interview.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20anything%2C%20that%20is%20a%20signal%20to%20them%20that%20you're%20not%20necessarily%20taking%20the%20interview%20seriously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20taking%20notes%20on%20your%20phone%20would%20be%20an%20even%20more%20serious%20error.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEspecially%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20ChatGPT%2C%20I've%20heard%20a%20lot%20of%20feedback%20from%20hiring%20teams%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20for%20technical%20roles%20like%20software%20engineering%20%E2%80%94%20that%20they%20never%20know%20if%20a%20candidate's%20work%20is%20fully%20theirs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lee%2C%20whose%20company%20specializes%20in%20prepping%20candidates%20for%20tech%20and%20finance%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20that%20context%2C%20doing%20your%20work%20on%20or%20taking%20notes%20on%20your%20phone%20could%20potentially%20come%20off%20as%20you%20cheating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20absolutely%20have%20to%20use%20technology%2C%20Toothacre%20suggests%20using%20an%20iPad%20instead%20of%20a%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2236a8706c-997e-4551-a5e5-fcf06fe18368%5C%22%3EGetting%20their%20extra-early%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20birds%20tend%20to%20get%20the%20worm%2C%20but%20showing%20up%20earlier%20than%2010-15%20minutes%20before%20your%20scheduled%20time%20could%20work%20against%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20too%20early%20could%20even%20inconvenience%20the%20team%2C%20especially%20if%20they%20staggered%20interviews%20on%20purpose%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToothacre%20added%20that%20the%2010-15-minute%20window%20shouldn't%20include%20time%20spent%20getting%20through%20security%20or%20finding%20the%20right%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20accessibility%20requirements%2C%20make%20sure%20to%20communicate%20with%20your%20recruiter%20beforehand%20about%20the%20building's%20access%20points%20so%20you%20don't%20lose%20time%20on%20the%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20arrive%20early%20because%20you%20live%20far%20away%20from%20the%20interview%20site%2C%20Lee%20suggests%20taking%20walks%20outside%20to%20calm%20your%20nervous%20system%20down%20a%20bit%20before%20heading%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22016f1a1d-8ea8-42b9-9b39-f0abbee3a846%5C%22%3EPiling%20on%20the%20perfume%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20definitely%20want%20to%20smell%20good%20when%20meeting%20with%20prospective%20employers%20in%20person%2C%20but%20overpowering%20perfume%20could%20be%20a%20turn-off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPerfume%20is%20a%20really%20fine%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Toothacre.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20not%20spray%20anything%20like%20right%20before%20you%20walk%20in%2C%20because%20it's%20probably%20not%20going%20to%20dissipate%20quickly%20enough%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20know%20who%20could%20have%20an%20allergy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToothacre%20advised%20finding%20a%20subtle%20scent%20or%20applying%20it%20an%20hour%20before%20the%20interview%20so%20there%20is%20still%20a%20hint%20of%20it%20but%20not%20enough%20to%20overwhelm%20someone%20in%20a%20closed%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20you%20will%20never%20have%20full%20control%20of%20whether%20you%20get%20hired%20or%20not%2C%20said%20Lee.%20%26quot%3BMy%20whole%20principle%20on%20interviewing%20is%20just%20to%20minimize%20as%20many%20potential%20red%20flags%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EReach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ahabraham%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehabraham%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20to%20share%20what%20your%20job-searching%20experience%20has%20been%20like.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20hre