83%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDonald%20Trump%20points%20to%20a%20selection%20of%20groceries%20at%20Trump%20National%20Golf%20Club%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%2FThe%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPresident-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20plans%20to%20implement%20new%20tariffs%2C%20and%20investors%20are%20bracing%20for%20impact.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETariffs%20tend%20to%20increase%20the%20prices%20of%20imports%2C%20potentially%20eating%20into%20corporate%20profits.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThree%20market%20experts%20share%20the%20eight%20companies%20that%20could%20be%20hit%20hardest.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20will%20be%20back%20in%20the%20White%20House%20next%20January%2C%20and%20he's%20bringing%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-higher-inflation-fed-interest-rates-taxes-mortgage-rates-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20first%20term%20in%20office%2C%20Trump%20imposed%20tariffs%20on%20steel%2C%20aluminum%2C%20and%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20Chinese%20imports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20president%20and%20now%20president-elect%20has%20been%20vocal%20about%20his%20support%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-trump-president-economy-tariffs-trade-war-kelly-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotectionist%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20election%20cycle.%20In%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20Trump%20has%20proposed%20policies%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20a%20blanket%20tariff%20of%20up%20to%2020%25%20on%20all%20imports%2C%20and%20up%20to%2060%25%20in%20the%20case%20of%20China%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20encouraging%20domestic%20manufacturing%20and%20reducing%20US%20dependence%20on%20foreign%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvestors%20generally%20are%20expecting%20some%20degree%20of%20tariffs.%20It's%20not%20just%20rhetoric%2C%26quot%3B%20Clayton%20Gardner%2C%20co-CEO%20of%20wealth%20management%20firm%20Titan%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20tax%20legislation%2C%20which%20needs%20to%20be%20voted%20on%20by%20Congress%2C%20tariffs%20can%20be%20implemented%20directly%20by%20the%20president%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Trump's%20made%20this%20issue%20one%20of%20his%20top%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20market%20experts%20say%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglobal-reaction-donald-trump-election-victory-tariffs-trade-disputes-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestors%20should%20brace%20themselves%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20impacts%20of%20such%20policies%20on%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20biggest%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e2730294-1871-4710-a6fc-4ab60cb2954d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20tariffs%20work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EImport%20tariffs%20work%20by%20placing%20an%20extra%20tax%20on%20goods%20or%20services%20entering%20a%20country.%20By%20artificially%20increasing%20the%20price%20of%20imports%2C%20tariffs%20boost%20demand%20for%20domestic%20products%20and%20shield%20domestic%20industries%20from%20foreign%20competition.%20But%20most%20economists%20argue%20that%20tariffs%20ultimately%20result%20in%20companies%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-election-victory-impact-investments-costs-housing-taxes-childcare-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsumers%3C%2Fa%3E%20alike%20being%20worse%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20faced%20with%20tariffs%2C%20companies%20importing%20products%20end%20up%20passing%20the%20effects%20down%20to%20consumers%20by%20raising%20prices%2C%20according%20to%20Jesus%20Salas%2C%20a%20finance%20professor%20at%20Lehigh%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20multinational%20corporations%2C%20this%20results%20in%20lower%20demand%20for%20their%20products%20and%20potentially%20lower%20profit%20margins%20due%20to%20higher%20prices%20and%20operating%20costs%2C%20Salas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20in%20the%20retail%2C%20consumer%20electronics%2C%20and%20automotive%20industries%20will%20be%20hit%20especially%20hard%2C%20as%20many%20of%20their%20business%20models%20source%20raw%20materials%20or%20base%20their%20operations%20overseas%2C%20according%20to%20Samuel%20Rines%2C%20a%20macro%20strategist%20at%20WisdomTree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuxury%20consumer%20goods%20brands%2C%20which%20have%20a%20large%20market%20in%20China%2C%20will%20be%20in%20for%20a%20rough%20time%2C%20added%20Gardner.%20These%20companies%20have%20historically%20had%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20their%20growth%20come%20from%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20companies%20with%20supply%20chains%20in%20China%20will%20be%20impacted%20the%20most%2C%20any%20country%20with%20foreign%20exposure%20is%20at%20risk%2C%20according%20to%20Salas%3A%20%26quot%3BAll%20companies%20that%20import%20products%20from%20Europe%2C%20Latin%20America%2C%20or%20China%20would%20be%20impacted.%26quot%3B%20For%20example%2C%20Trump%20has%20recently%20threatened%20a%2025%25%20tariff%20on%20all%20products%20from%20Mexico.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20the%20possibility%20of%20counter-tariffs.%20In%202018%2C%20Canada%2C%20China%2C%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20India%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Turkey%20reacted%20to%20US%20tariffs%20on%20steel%20and%20aluminum%20and%20foreign%20products%20with%20tariffs%20of%20their%20own.%20This%20made%20American%20exports%20such%20as%20agricultural%20products%20more%20expensive%20overseas%20and%20hurt%20US%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCorporate%20America%20is%20very%2C%20very%20global%20in%20its%20investment%20base.%20It's%20very%2C%20very%20reliant%20in%20some%20cases%20on%20non-US%20sales%20and%20revenues%20for%20their%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Rines%20said.%20A%20deterioration%20in%20trade%20relations%20could%20lead%20to%20decreased%20revenues%20from%20important%20overseas%20customers%2C%20resulting%20in%20lower%20profits%20and%20shareholder%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cfffb692-6aca-4bb1-bb11-10f07698745f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETariffs%202.0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20might%20think%20that%20if%20these%20companies%20lived%20through%20the%20first%20Trump%20administration's%20tariffs%2C%20they%20should%20have%20already%20prepared%20their%20supply%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20largely%20not%20the%20case%2C%20according%20to%20Salas.%20Although%20companies%20did%20move%20some%20of%20their%20operations%20out%20of%20China%20as%20a%20result%20of%20Trump's%20tariffs%20the%20first%20time%20around%2C%20there's%20insufficient%20labor%20supply%20in%20the%20US%20to%20meet%20the%20demands%20of%20some%20large%20companies%20like%20Apple%2C%20in%20his%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearshoring%2C%20or%20bringing%20operations%20closer%20to%20the%20US%20to%20places%20in%20Central%20America%2C%20has%20been%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20recent%20years%20as%20corporations%20worry%20about%20exposure%20to%20China.%20But%20this%20doesn't%20protect%20companies%20from%20the%20effects%20of%20Trump%20tariffs%20either%2C%20as%20seen%20by%20Trump's%20proposal%20for%20aggressive%20tariffs%20on%20Mexican%20imports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20factories%20are%20expensive%20and%20take%20a%20long%20time%20to%20build.%20Since%20tariffs%20are%20exercised%20at%20the%20discretion%20of%20individual%20presidents%2C%20corporations%20might%20decide%20it's%20not%20worth%20it%20to%20completely%20reroute%20their%20supply%20chain%20for%20a%20transitory%20policy%20that%20could%20change%20in%20four%20years%2C%20added%20Salas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20that%20companies%20haven't%20taken%20any%20steps%20to%20localize%20their%20supply%20chains.%20Walmart%20has%20been%20increasing%20its%20imports%20from%20India%20and%20cutting%20back%20on%20sourcing%20from%20China%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20according%20to%20Rines.%20However%2C%20large%20corporations%20stil